  "issue_number": 5678,
  "issue_title": "`transform` callback `ctx.addIssue` not in Typescript",
  "issue_body": "According to the source (and various articles) I can see that a transform callback receives a context object containing an `addIssue` method:\n\n```ts\nconst schema = z.transform((value, ctx) => {\n  if(isNotValid(value)) {\n    ctx.addIssue({\n      code: \"invalid_element\",\n      message: \"Not valid\",\n    });\n  }\n  return value;\n});\n\nschema.parse(someValue);\n```\n\nThis work at runtime. However, in Typescript I get an error telling me `addIssue` doesn't exist.\n\nIs this method deprecated? It certainly wasn't removed, and TS doesn't mark it as deprecated, but rather absent completely.\n\nConfirmed in Zod v4.2.1 and v4.3.6 (presumably between as well).\n\n-----\n\nResolution:\n\nA. If the method is deprecated, the Typescript needs to be updated to indicate that it's deprecated, but not absent (until it is in fact removed).\n\nB. If the method is *not* deprecated, it needs to be added to the Typescript definition.",
  "merged_at": "2026-04-27T16:07:06Z",
